{"article_id":"z1pSJGTN7dvQtU1W","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Hear Marilyn Geewax On 'Tell Me More '","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"Does Jobs Report","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"Mean Things Are Getting Better ?","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"Does Jobs Report","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"Mean Things Are Getting Better ?","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"Listen · 11:45","depth":3},{"id":6,"text":"11:45","depth":3},{"id":7,"text":"With a new report","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"showing","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"the nation 's unemployment rate fell to 7.8 percent last month ,","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"the Obama administration got good news Friday :","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"Jobs are indeed growing .","depth":5},{"id":12,"text":"But ,","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"as Republicans noted ,","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"the pace remains well below the level","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"needed to provide paychecks for the 12.1 million people","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"seeking them .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"The truth is , each party could find evidence","depth":5},{"id":18,"text":"to support either a positive or negative spin on the labor market ,","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"which is recovering","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"- yet weak .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"At a Friday campaign rally in Virginia , President Obama focused on the continued growth .","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"He said","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"the jobs report is `` a reminder","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"that this country has come too far","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"to turn back now . ''","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"Republican candidate Mitt Romney saw something very different .","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"`` If not for all the people","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"who have simply dropped out of the labor force ,","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"the real unemployment rate would be closer to 11 percent , ''","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"he said in a statement .","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"The competing views both have validity .","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"Before considering the spin ,","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"here are the facts :","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"All this year , the unemployment rate had been vacillating in a narrow range between 8.3 percent and 8.1 percent ,","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"where it stood in August .","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"But the rate fell to 7.8 percent in September ,","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"after a household survey showed","depth":14},{"id":38,"text":"more people say","depth":15},{"id":39,"text":"they are working .","depth":15},{"id":40,"text":"The Labor Department also revised some summer data .","depth":14},{"id":41,"text":"August payrolls actually rose by 142,000 , better than the initially reported 96,000 ,","depth":14},{"id":42,"text":"while July was revised up to 181,000 , from an earlier estimate of 141,000 .","depth":14},{"id":43,"text":"Last month , employers added 114,000 jobs , almost exactly what economists had predicted .","depth":14},{"id":44,"text":"The pace of improvement is far too slow","depth":13},{"id":45,"text":"to absorb the backlog of people","depth":14},{"id":46,"text":"seeking work .","depth":14},{"id":47,"text":"About 100,000 new jobs are needed each month","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"simply to keep pace with population growth .","depth":13},{"id":49,"text":"The jobless rate would be much higher today","depth":14},{"id":50,"text":"- more like the 11 percent","depth":15},{"id":51,"text":"Romney notes -","depth":15},{"id":52,"text":"if labor force participation were as high","depth":14},{"id":53,"text":"as when Obama took office .","depth":14},{"id":54,"text":"Many people have dropped out of the workplace ,","depth":14},{"id":55,"text":"either to take early retirement ,","depth":15},{"id":56,"text":"go back to school","depth":16},{"id":57,"text":"or to stay home ,","depth":16},{"id":58,"text":"because they do n't see much hope","depth":14},{"id":59,"text":"of finding a good job .","depth":14},{"id":60,"text":"To return to , say , 6 percent unemployment within three years ,","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"economists say","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"employers need to be adding about 375,000 workers a month .","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"In January 2009 ,","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"when Obama took the oath of office ,","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"the U.S. economy lost more than 800,000 jobs .","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"By spurring Congress to immediately pass the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act ,","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"the president turned around that employment plunge","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"and `` kept our economy from swerving over the cliff , ''","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"according to Rebecca Thiess , a policy analyst at the Economic Policy Institute , a left-leaning research group .","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"The nonpartisan Congressional Budget Office says","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"the stimulus created up to 3.3 million full-time jobs","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"and helped stabilize the labor market in the 2009-2011 period .","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"Since the recovery kicked in ,","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"the private sector has added jobs for 31 straight months ,","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"bringing the total to 5.2 million new jobs .","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"The past three-and-a-half years could be considered a split decision , with good points and bad .","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"But what lies ahead ?","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"Romney says","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"his economic policies would create about 12 million jobs over the next four years .","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"But many independent economists say","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"that 's the same number of jobs","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"that would be created under current policies .","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"Joseph Davis , chief economist for the mutual fund giant Vanguard , said","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"he does n't see the unemployment rate improving significantly","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"until Congress takes definitive action","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"to reduce the deficit and the debt .","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"Having lawmakers constantly put off major decisions about taxes and spending is creating tremendous uncertainties for employers","depth":5},{"id":88,"text":"who feel","depth":6},{"id":89,"text":"they ca n't make hiring plans","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"until they know what their taxes will be","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"and whether government spending","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"- on infrastructure , defense contracts and more -","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"will continue .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"`` If we do n't see a meaningful change","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"in terms","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"of clearing up policy uncertainty ,","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"then it 's very difficult to see the economic trajectory change , ''","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"Davis said .","depth":6},{"id":99,"text":"`` If we could adopt a credible and binding plan","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"to reduce the deficit ,","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"that would go a long way in reducing uncertainty ''","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"and opening the door to new employees ,","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"he added .","depth":6},{"id":104,"text":"Friday 's big move in the jobless rate did not go unnoticed by Romney supporters ,","depth":6},{"id":105,"text":"many of whom suggested","depth":7},{"id":106,"text":"the Labor Department manipulated the data .","depth":7},{"id":107,"text":"For example , Jack Welch , the retired CEO of General Electric , tweeted","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"that the drop in the jobless rate was `` unbelievable , ''","depth":7},{"id":109,"text":"and added this reference to Obama :","depth":7},{"id":110,"text":"`` ca n't debate ,","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"so change numbers . ''","depth":8},{"id":112,"text":"The Bureau of Labor Statistics has a reputation for honest work .","depth":6},{"id":113,"text":"The monthly jobs report is put together by dozens of career professionals","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"who tabulate and analyze data .","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"Mainstream economists say","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"that with so many people involved , manipulating data is extremely implausible .","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"Labor Secretary Hilda Solis ,","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"speaking on CNBC ,","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"the jobs report is reliable .","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"`` These are our best-trained and best-skilled individuals","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"working in the BLS ,","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"and it 's really ludicrous to hear that kind of statement '' from Welch ,","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"she said .","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"The BLS report is supported by an independent measure ,","depth":7},{"id":126,"text":"which found similar results .","depth":7},{"id":127,"text":"Gallup , the polling company , calculated","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"that September 's unemployment rate ,","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"without seasonal adjustments ,","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"fell to 7.9 percent ,","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"which was `` the lowest [ level ]","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"Gallup has recorded","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"since it began collecting employment data in January 2010 . ''","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":267,"left":140,"right":266,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":140,"left":138,"right":139,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":138,"left":136,"right":137,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":136,"left":0,"right":135,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":135,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":137,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":139,"left":5,"right